TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Framework for Analyzing Customer Service Orientations in Manufacturing
AU  - Bowen, David E.
AU  - Siehl, Caren
AU  - Schneider, Benjamin
Y1  - 1989/01/01
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1989.4279005
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1989.4279005
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 75
EP  - 95
VL  - 14
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The proposed framework first clarifies the concept of customer service in a manufacturing context. Then the key strategic choices associated with emphasizing a customer service?oriented strategy are specified. Next, the organizational arrangements necessary to implement these strategic choices are described. Finally, alternative effective configurations of the strategic choices, organizational arrangements, and customer service activities are proposed. Research propositions are presented that focus on the relationship between central contingencies in the strategic management literature and customer service in manufacturing.
AB  - The proposed framework first clarifies the concept of customer service in a manufacturing context. Then the key strategic choices associated with emphasizing a customer service?oriented strategy are specified. Next, the organizational arrangements necessary to implement these strategic choices are described. Finally, alternative effective configurations of the strategic choices, organizational arrangements, and customer service activities are proposed. Research propositions are presented that focus on the relationship between central contingencies in the strategic management literature and customer service in manufacturing.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1989.4279005
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1989.4279005
